### CSS Box Model

The box model consists of content, padding, border, and margin layers. By default (content-box), width only includes content. With border-box, width includes padding and border, making sizing more predictable.

```css
.box {
  width: 200px;
  padding: 20px;
  border: 5px solid black;
  margin: 10px;
  box-sizing: border-box; /* Total width stays 200px */
}
```

**Common interview trap:** Forgetting that margin is outside the border and doesn't affect element width.

